    "sections": [
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Introduction",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.1",
            "summary": "This supervisory statement is addressed to UK Solvency II firms and to the Society of Lloyd’s. It sets out how the Prudential Regulation Authority (PRA) expects to deal with firms in the circumstances",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.2",
            "summary": "[Deleted]",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.3",
            "summary": "This statement should be read alongside all relevant Parts of the PRA Rulebook, including the Undertakings in Difficulty Part, and the relevant powers under FS",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.4",
            "summary": "This statement expands on the PRA’s general approach as set out in its insurance approach document.1 By clearly and consistently explaining its expectations of firms in relation to the particular area",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "1.5",
            "summary": "This statement has been subject to public consultation2 and reflects the feedback that was received by the PRA.",
            "as_at_date": "20/03/2015"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "chapter_number": "",
        "chapter_title": "Firms in breach of the minimum capital requirement",
        "paragraphs": [
          {
            "paragraph_number": "2.1",
            "summary": "The PRA will take the same approach to firms which are failing to meet the MCR, whether they are still being run by their directors or whether an administrator or liquidator has been appointed.",
            "as_at_date": "20/03/2015"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "2.2",
            "summary": "The PRA expects those firms to act in a way which avoids significant systemic disruption, while protecting vital economic functions and which ensures that policyholders are appropriately protected. Th",
            "as_at_date": "20/03/2015"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "2.3",
            "summary": "The PRA will be particularly concerned to ensure that:",
            "as_at_date": "20/03/2015"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "2.4",
            "summary": "The PRA will require a firm with no realistic prospect of prompt restoration of compliance with the MCR to bring its business to a close in as rapid and orderly manner as is consistent with the genera",
            "as_at_date": "20/03/2015"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "2.5",
            "summary": "A firm in this position will not be permitted by the PRA to effect new contracts of insurance but the firm may be permitted to continue activities necessary to carry out existing contracts in a manner",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          },
          {
            "paragraph_number": "2.6",
            "summary": "The PRA will seek to exercise its powers under FSMA (and in particular, section 55M) by imposing an assets requirement on a firm which is failing to meet the MCR and is unable to rectify this. The pur",
            "as_at_date": "31/12/2024"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
